      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/55/2",
      "text": [
        " أَوَّلُ مَمْلُوكٍ أَمْلِكُهُ فَهُوَ حُرٌّ فَأَصَابَ سِتَّةً فَقَالَ \"إِنَّمَا كَانَتْ نِيَّتُهُ عَلَى وَاحِدٍ فَلْيَخْتَرْ أَيَّهُمْ شَاءَ فَلْيُعْتِقْهُ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3558 - Al-Hasan al-Sayqal asked about a man who said: \"The first slave I acquire will be free.\" Then he acquired six slaves.\nImam (as) said: \"His intention was for one. Let him choose whichever one he wishes and set him free.\""
        ]
      }
    },
